    "question_id" : 9489384,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>If you want a balance between capability and readability, you may combine both approaches:</p>\n<pre class=\"lang-java prettyprint-override\"><code>ImmutableMap&lt;String,String&gt; myMap = ImmutableMap.&lt;String, String&gt;builder()\n    .putAll(ImmutableMap.of(\n        &quot;key1&quot;, &quot;value1&quot;, \n        &quot;key2&quot;, &quot;value2&quot;, \n        &quot;key3&quot;, &quot;value3&quot;, \n        &quot;key4&quot;, &quot;value4&quot;));\n    .putAll(ImmutableMap.of(\n        &quot;key5&quot;, &quot;value5&quot;, \n        &quot;key6&quot;, &quot;value6&quot;, \n        &quot;key7&quot;, &quot;value7&quot;, \n        &quot;key8&quot;, &quot;value8&quot;, \n        &quot;key9&quot;, &quot;value9&quot;));\n    .build();\n</code></pre>\n<p>Whether or not this is a good idea, is something open to discussion.</p>\n"
  } ],
